## Setup checklist (for you, before offering these)

1. **Add these files to your `3day-scopes` repo** in a new `/widgets/` folder:
   - `widgets/observatory.html`
   - `widgets/moon.html`
   - `widgets/correspondences.html`
2. **Commit + push.** GitHub Pages will serve them automatically at:
   - `https://slaing77.github.io/3day-scopes/widgets/observatory.html`
   - `https://slaing77.github.io/3day-scopes/widgets/moon.html`
   - `https://slaing77.github.io/3day-scopes/widgets/correspondences.html`
3. **CORS check** — these fetch from `horoscopes.darkfoliopress.com`, and since
   the widgets can now be embedded on *any* third-party domain (not just your
   own), your API needs `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` (or an open policy)
   rather than a single allowed domain — otherwise other people's sites won't
   be able to load the data.
4. **Endpoint paths (confirmed):**
   - `GET https://horoscopes.darkfoliopress.com/api/wix/observatory`
   - `GET https://horoscopes.darkfoliopress.com/api/wix/moon`
   - `GET https://horoscopes.darkfoliopress.com/api/public/oracle/today` (used for the Correspondence widget — herb/gem/rune)

   The Observatory and Moon endpoints' exact JSON field names weren't
   confirmed yet, so those two widgets' JS tries several likely key
   spellings and logs the raw response to the browser console. Open each
   widget page, check the console, and if any fields are blank, send me the
   raw JSON and I'll lock in the exact field names in one pass.

## Sizing notes
Each widget is designed for a **360px-wide sidebar-style placement**. On Wix,
set the embed element's width to match (or leave "responsive" on if Wix
offers it) — the widget itself has `max-width` built in so it won't overflow
on mobile.
